==English==

===Etymology===
Patented 1823 by Charles Mackintosh (1766 – 1843).

===Alternative forms===
* [[macintosh]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''mackintosh'''|'''mackintoshes'''}}

#A waterproof coat or [[raincoat]]
#*Happiness - written by A.A. Milne
:John had great big waterproof boots on;
:John had a great big waterproof hat;
:John had a great big waterproof '''mackintosh''' --
:And that (Said John) is that.

